This paper proposes a parallel stochastic gradient descent algorithm for linear learners, which is a common technique in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the parallelization of the algorithm, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper evaluates the algorithm's accuracy and performance on datasets, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
